# Deploying nginx on Kubernetes (CloudStack CKS) with HAProxy Ingress

This document covers deploying a sample nginx application on a CloudStack
CKS Kubernetes cluster, exposing it to the internet using the **HAProxy
Kubernetes Ingress Controller**, and explains the full request flow from
client to pod.

> **Why HAProxy Ingress and not ingress-nginx?**
> The community `ingress-nginx` project (`kubernetes/ingress-nginx`) was
> retired by Kubernetes SIG Network in November 2025, with best-effort
> maintenance ending in March 2026 — no further releases, bugfixes, or
> security patches. HAProxy Ingress (`haproxytech/kubernetes-ingress`) is
> actively maintained and used here instead.
> Details: https://kubernetes.io/blog/2025/11/11/ingress-nginx-retirement/

---

## 1. Architecture overview

```
Internet
   │
   ▼
CloudStack Public IP  (Firewall: allow TCP/443, TCP/80)
   │
   ▼
CloudStack Load Balancer rule
   public:443 → NodePort 31187  (round robin across worker nodes)
   public:80  → NodePort 31666  (round robin across worker nodes)
   │
   ▼
Kubernetes Worker Nodes (kube-proxy / iptables-IPVS)
   │
   ▼
HAProxy Ingress Controller pods  (namespace: haproxy-controller)
   - Terminates TLS
   - Reads the `Ingress` object to decide routing by Host header
   │
   ▼
Service: web-app-svc (ClusterIP, namespace: web)
   │
   ▼
nginx pods (Deployment: web-app, 3 replicas, namespace: web)
```

---

## 2. Prerequisites

- A working CKS (or any Kubernetes) cluster, `kubectl` configured against it
- `helm` installed on a machine with access to the cluster (see §3.1)
- A CloudStack public IP already associated with the network the cluster's
  worker nodes are on

---

## 3. Deploy the application

### 3.1 Namespace

```bash
kubectl create namespace web
```

### 3.2 Deployment + ConfigMaps

Save as `01-deployment.yaml`:

```yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: web-app
  namespace: web
  labels:
    app: web-app
spec:
  replicas: 3
  revisionHistoryLimit: 5
  strategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
    rollingUpdate:
      maxSurge: 1
      maxUnavailable: 0
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: web-app
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: web-app
    spec:
      securityContext:
        runAsNonRoot: true
        runAsUser: 101
        fsGroup: 101
        seccompProfile:
          type: RuntimeDefault
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.27-alpine
        ports:
        - name: http
          containerPort: 8080
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 500m
            memory: 256Mi
        securityContext:
          allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
          readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
          capabilities:
            drop: ["ALL"]
        volumeMounts:
        - name: nginx-conf
          mountPath: /etc/nginx/conf.d
          readOnly: true
        - name: nginx-cache
          mountPath: /var/cache/nginx
        - name: nginx-run
          mountPath: /var/run
        - name: html
          mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html
          readOnly: true
        readinessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /healthz
            port: http
          initialDelaySeconds: 5
          periodSeconds: 10
        livenessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /healthz
            port: http
          initialDelaySeconds: 10
          periodSeconds: 20
      volumes:
      - name: nginx-conf
        configMap:
          name: web-app-nginx-conf
      - name: nginx-cache
        emptyDir: {}
      - name: nginx-run
        emptyDir: {}
      - name: html
        configMap:
          name: web-app-html
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: web-app-nginx-conf
  namespace: web
data:
  default.conf: |
    server {
      listen 8080;
      server_name _;
      location /healthz {
        access_log off;
        return 200 "ok\n";
        add_header Content-Type text/plain;
      }
      location / {
        root /usr/share/nginx/html;
        index index.html;
      }
    }
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: web-app-html
  namespace: web
data:
  index.html: |
    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html>
      <head><title>web-app</title></head>
      <body><h1>Hello from web-app</h1></body>
    </html>
```

> **Note:** no PersistentVolume is used here. `nginx-conf` and `html` are
> `configMap` volumes (static config injected at mount time); `nginx-cache`
> and `nginx-run` are `emptyDir` (scratch space, wiped on pod restart). This
> app is stateless, so no persistent storage is required.

```bash
kubectl apply -f 01-deployment.yaml
kubectl -n web rollout status deployment/web-app
```

### 3.3 Service (ClusterIP)

Save as `02-service.yaml`:

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: web-app-svc
  namespace: web
  labels:
    app: web-app
spec:
  selector:
    app: web-app
  ports:
  - name: http
    port: 80
    targetPort: http
  type: ClusterIP
```

```bash
kubectl apply -f 02-service.yaml
```

`ClusterIP` is correct here — the Service only needs to be reachable from
inside the cluster (by the Ingress controller); it is never exposed
directly to the internet.

