## 5. TLS certificate

The Ingress controller terminates TLS — the nginx pods never handle
certificates themselves. Create a Secret containing the cert/key that the
Ingress references:

```bash
# For testing with a non-public/test hostname, a self-signed cert is fine:
openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -keyout privkey.pem -out fullchain.pem \
  -subj "/CN=app.test.com"

kubectl create secret tls web-app-tls \
  --cert=fullchain.pem --key=privkey.pem -n web
```

For a real public domain, use [cert-manager](https://cert-manager.io/) with
a Let's Encrypt `ClusterIssuer` instead of a self-signed cert (see the
`cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer` annotation in §6).

