## 7. Expose to the internet via CloudStack

### 7.1 Firewall rule

Allow inbound TCP/443 (and TCP/80, for the HTTP→HTTPS redirect) on the
public IP associated with the cluster's network.

### 7.2 Load Balancer rule

Since the HAProxy controller runs multiple replicas across different
worker nodes, use a CloudStack **Load Balancer** rule (not a single
port-forwarding rule) so traffic is distributed across all worker node
IPs on the controller's NodePort:

```bash
cmk create loadbalancerrule \
  publicipid=<public-ip-id> \
  algorithm=roundrobin \
  name=web-app-https \
  privateport=31187 \
  publicport=443 \
  networkid=<network-id>

cmk assign loadbalancerrule \
  id=<lb-rule-id> \
  virtualmachineids=<worker-vm-id-1>,<worker-vm-id-2>
```

Repeat for port 80 → NodePort 31666 if you want the HTTP redirect path
reachable too.

### 7.3 Point DNS (or hosts file, for testing) at the public IP

```
app.test.com  →  <cloudstack-public-ip>
```

### 7.4 Verify

```bash
curl -v https://app.test.com/
```

