        Service: web-app-svc (ClusterIP)
        10.105.32.113:80
                      |
            kube-proxy / iptables
                      |
        +-------------+-------------+
        |             |             |
        v             v             v
 web-app Pod1   web-app Pod2   web-app Pod3

Since your HAProxy Ingress Service is of type LoadBalancer, the request flow is different from a NodePort-based Ingress.

Your HAProxy Service is:

Service: haproxy-ingress-kubernetes-ingress
Type: LoadBalancer
External IP: 103.232.25.186
Ports:
  80  -> 30332 (NodePort)
  443 -> 31216 (NodePort)

Although Kubernetes automatically allocates NodePorts (30332 and 31216), clients on the Internet do not use them directly. The external load balancer created by your cloud provider (in your case, Apache CloudStack through its Cloud Controller Manager) forwards traffic to those NodePorts.

## 9. Troubleshooting notes from this deployment

- **`ADDRESS` blank in `kubectl get ingress`**: expected with a `NodePort`
  Service — there's no single external address to report, since traffic
  arrives per-node. Not a failure.
- **Redirect goes to `:8443` instead of `:443`**: fix the controller's
  `ssl-redirect-port` ConfigMap key (see §4.3).
- **`curl https://<public-ip>/` returns 404**: expected if the request's
  `Host` header doesn't match a rule in the `Ingress` (e.g. hitting the
  raw IP directly, which sets `Host: <ip>`, not `Host: app.test.com`).
  Test with `curl -H "Host: app.test.com" https://<public-ip>/` before DNS
  is in place.
- **No response reaching the node externally**: use `tcpdump -i any port
  <nodeport> -n` on the node while testing from outside — if no packets
  arrive, the issue is in the CloudStack firewall/LB/ACL layer, not
  Kubernetes. If packets arrive but nothing responds, check node-level
  `iptables`/security groups.
- **VPC tier networks**: if the cluster's network is a VPC tier rather
  than an Isolated network, Network ACL rules are required in addition to
  firewall/port-forwarding rules, since VPC tiers route through ACLs.
